    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3; this gap is accepted given the standardised F1717 protocol and multi-laboratory corroboration. The primary ValidationResult (vr-cou1-stiffness-yield-force) was generated under model configuration ansys-mechanical-2026-q1-build-7-rc2. The modelling team has documented that no solver patches affecting structural contact or nonlinear material integration were applied between the rc2 release candidate and the ansys-mechanical-2026-q1-build-7 general availability release, and considers the two builds effectively identical for this application. On this basis the credibility package is accepted and the FEA framework is considered credible for the stated COU.",
